snippet.textDisplay: We all know that Leeds have played by far the best football in the league this season. No one can touch them when it comes to possession and creating chances. We missed out last season because we couldn't put chances away and finish off worse teams. We're even better this season except we still don't have a proven goal scorer. Can someone please explain why Bielsa and those above him have done nothing to solve the problem? The football is brilliant, but we still have no genuine striker after 2 years? It makes no sense. We'd be almost out of reach by now and looking forward to next year in the Prem if we only had a true striker. Bielsa isn't stupid. The club aren't broke. So what's going on? Why no legit pre-season signing (or a truly good recruit in January)? Don't they want Leeds in the Premier League? Am I missing something?

snippet.textDisplay: Not trying to ruin the mood or anything but I think we got lucky here today. The score could easily have been the other way round. We've had games just like this one that didn't go our way. The rest of the championship has figured out how to stop us in our tracks. Crowd the box as if they're defending a 1-0 lead in the 89th minute and wait for us to over extend, then counter attack quickly. It nearly worked for them a couple of times today. Tactics need refreshing if we are to be sure of promotion. We're not in the clear yet
